The paper discusses improvements to the PC algorithm, which is a widely used algorithm in machine learning and causal inference. The focus is on improving accuracy and scalability, which are key concerns in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the use of statistical tests and optimization techniques, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
